18/03/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Local media reported on Friday (18 March) that Tirana will host a business and investment summit in late April. 
The focus will be on boosting investments and encouraging business in Albania and throughout the Balkans. 
Government officials and business representatives from more than 20 countries are expected to participate. 
The economy ministry and the Albanian Foreign Investment Promotion Agency are sponsoring the event. 
(Albanian Daily News - 18/03/05)
